parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause the vehicle to stall, jerk, or hesitate while driving, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls or jerks while driving
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle is unable to accelerate properly
the vehicle rolls backwards when driving uphill
the RPM fluctuates
the vehicle emits a burning smell.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the airbag system can lead to a failure to deploy in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The airbag light is on or flashing
the airbag system is loose
the AC compressor is locked
the belt is broken
the pulley is not working
the AC condenser needs to be repaired.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the powertrain and catalyst systems can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The powertrain has catalyst issues
the exhaust is leaking at the manifold and catalyst
the oxygen sensors are slow to respond
the exhaust connections are faulty.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the ABS system can cause the vehicle to jerk or hesitate, leading to potential accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The ABS light is on
the transmission jerks or hesitates
the vehicle lunges forward
the vehicle needs to be restarted multiple times.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants of the vehicle are not provided with the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Malfunctions in the airbag system can cause the airbags to deploy unexpectedly, resulting in injuries or accidents, or fail to deploy in the event of a crash, leading to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
airbags deploy unexpectedly
airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The recall of Takata airbags can lead to the deployment of faulty airbags, causing injuries or fatalities, or the failure of airbags to deploy in the event of a crash, resulting in serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Airbag warning light illuminates on the dashboard
receipt of recall notification
airbags deploy unexpectedly
airbags fail to deploy in the event of a crash
resulting in injuries or fatalities.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the CVT transmission can cause hesitation, jerking, and loss of power when accelerating, making it difficult to control the vehicle, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Hesitation when accelerating
jerking or stuttering when shifting gears
clunking noise from the transmission
severe vibrations when the car is in motion
vehicle wanders back and forth on the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the electrical system can cause the engine to stall, leading to loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Engine light is on
vehicle stops running when the heater or A/C is turned on
dashboard lights up with multiple warning lights
vehicle may be defective in some way.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the steering system can cause the vehicle to veer off course, making it difficult to control, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: Vehicle veers off to one side
steering wheel feels loose or unstable
vehicle wanders back and forth on the road
steering wheel locks up.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition system can cause the vehicle to stall or fail to start, leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: Key won't turn in the ignition
key needs to be wiggled for several minutes to start the vehicle
vehicle fails to start.
